9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 51, L.D. 33, “An Act to Amend the Laws
10 Governing Fantasy Contests”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 8 MRSA §1101, sub-§4, ¶A, as enacted by PL 2017, c. 303, §2, is amended
14 to read:
15 A. One Two or more fantasy contestants per game or contest, none of which may be
16 the fantasy contest operator, pay an entry fee to participate;
17 Sec. 2. 8 MRSA §1105, sub-§2, as enacted by PL 2017, c. 303, §2, is amended to
18 read:
19 2. Allocation of funds. The director shall collect for deposit to the General Fund 10%
20 of gross fantasy contest revenues, including any revenues earned while operating pending
21 approval of an application submitted to the director as described in section 1103, subsection
22 9, from a fantasy contest operator licensed under this chapter that has gross fantasy contest
23 revenues of $100,000 or greater.'
24 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
25 number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment replaces the bill. It updates the definition of "fantasy contest" to mean
2288 a game or contest in which 2 or more contestants, none of which may be the fantasy contest
2299 operator, pay an entry fee to participate. The amendment removes the definition of
3300 "proposition bet" from the bill and the prohibition on fantasy contests based on proposition
3311 betting. The amendment removes from the bill changes to the initial and renewal fee for a
3322 license for a fantasy contest operator and removes the repeal of the provision of law
3333 allowing a fantasy contest operator to operate a fantasy contest while an initial license,
3344 license renewal or license transfer is pending. The amendment also provides that the
